title: the GEORGE WALLINGTON trios / 1952 OJC limited edition
description:
Giacinto Figlia aka George Wallington (1924-1993) was a highly regarded "bop" 

pianist.  This is the second of his 10 albums listed on Wikipedia.


Mingus on the first 4 tracks.  His bass sound on track 1: LOVE BEAT, is very

unusual.  At first I thought it might be an electric bass because there's

a sustained quality to it.  Somehow I can't quite picture Mingus playing an 

electric bass.
